com.maxmind.geoip2.model

Class City

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.maxmind.geoip2.model.Country
      • com.maxmind.geoip2.model.City
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CityIspOrg, Omni

    public class City
extends Country
    This class provides a model for the data returned by the GeoIP2 City end point. The only difference between the City, City/ISP/Org, and Omni model classes is which fields in each record may be populated.
    See Also:
    GeoIP2 Web Services

      • getSubdivisionsList

        public List<SubdivisionRecord> getSubdivisionsList()
        Returns:
        An List of SubdivisionRecord objects representing the country subdivisions for the requested IP address. The number and type of subdivisions varies by country, but a subdivision is typically a state, province, county, etc. Subdivisions are ordered from most general (largest) to most specific (smallest). If the response did not contain any subdivisions, this method returns an empty array.

      • getMostSpecificSubdivision

        public SubdivisionRecord getMostSpecificSubdivision()
        Returns:
        An object representing the most specific subdivision returned. If the response did not contain any subdivisions, this method returns an empty SubdivisionRecord object.
